data.description: Casual elegance describes this absolutely beautiful, one of a kind, showcase home, located within walking distance of the shops and restaurants of downtown Alpharetta! This home and property are truly unique in the market. The house, which started as a typical 1960s era red brick ranch style home, has been opened up, expanded, and completely transformed inside and out into a modern farmhouse style home with an open concept floor plan. The fenced back yard is an entertainer's dream featuring a two level deck, hot tub, fire pit, outdoor refrigerator, 16 person picnic table, a water feature, and low maintenance plantings and patios, all anchored by a beautiful, vine covered pergola. Can you picture yourself hosting wonderful summertime BBQs here, or gathering around the fire pit with your s'mores in the cooler seasons? The renovations include an expanded primary suite with an aromatherapy/steam shower addition and a two person walk in closet and exercise nook, expanded great room and home office addition, a screened porch addition, front porch addition, powder room addition, new board and batten siding, roof, windows, HVAC, upgraded insulation, lighting, flooring, doors and plumbing fixtures, and too many more items to list! Please inquire for a complete list which is available with the listing documents. For veterans and military personnel, there is an assumable VA loan in place. All this, together with the ability to walk to downtown Alpharetta, take a run on the Alpha Loop, or drive a few short minutes to Avalon or Georgia 400 make this property the perfect place to call home!
